---
import BaseLayout from 'src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .intro {
            font-size: 20px;
            color: #555;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 28px;
            color: #34495e;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul, ol {
            margin: 15px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        code {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 5px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            color: #c0392b;
        }

        .code-example {
            background-color: #ecf0f1;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            font-family: monospace;
        }

        .highlight {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding-top: 10px;
            border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
            color: #777;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
    </style>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/bloglist" style="display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #3498db;">&larr; Back</a>
        <header>
            <h1>Git Version Control Basics</h1>
            <p class="intro">Learn the fundamentals of Git for efficient code management and collaboration.</p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2>What is Git? ü§î</h2>
            <p>Imagine you're writing a story, and you want to keep all different versions of it. That's exactly what Git does for your code! It's like a time machine for your project that lets you:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Track every change you make üìù</li>
                <li>Work with others without stepping on each other's toes üë•</li>
                <li>Experiment with new ideas safely üî¨</li>
                <li>Travel back in time to working versions ‚è∞</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Getting Started with Git üöÄ</h2>
            <h3>Essential Commands</h3>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`# Initialize a new Git repository
git init

# Check status of your changes
git status

# Add files to staging area
git add .

# Commit your changes
git commit -m "Made something awesome! üéâ"`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Branching - Your New Superpower üí™</h2>
            <p>Branches let you work on different versions of your project simultaneously. Think of them as parallel universes!</p>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`# Create a new branch
git branch feature-awesome

# Switch to the branch
git checkout feature-awesome

# Or do both at once
git checkout -b new-feature`}</pre></code>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Branch Workflow Visualization</h3>
            <pre style="background: #f4f4f4; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px;">
main      : o---o---o---o
            \
feature   :  o---o---o
                  \
bugfix    :        o---o
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Collaboration Made Easy ü§ù</h2>
            <h3>Working with Remotes</h3>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`# Clone a repository
git clone https://github.com/awesome/project.git

# Push your changes
git push origin main

# Get latest changes
git pull origin main`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Pro Tips for Git Masters üéØ</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Commit early, commit often!</li>
                <li>Write clear commit messages</li>
                <li>Create a .gitignore file for files you don't want to track</li>
                <li>Always pull before you push</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Common Scenarios and Solutions üÜò</h2>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`# Oops! Wrong commit message
git commit --amend -m "Better message"

# Undo last commit but keep changes
git reset HEAD~1 --soft

# Discard all local changes
git reset --hard HEAD`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p>&copy; 2024 Learn2Code | Empowering beginners to dive into programming</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
